Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian using the word "sudijo" in different forms and positions:

1. *Sudijo*, da li ste doneli odluku? (Judge, have you made a decision?)
2. Molim vas, *sudijo*, da obratite pažnju na ovaj dokaz. (Please, Your Honor, pay attention to this evidence.)
3. Nakon dugog suđenja, *sudijo* je konačno izrekao presudu. (After a long trial, the judge finally pronounced the verdict.)
4. *Sudijo*, molim vas da mi objasnite značenje ovog pravnog termina. (Judge, please explain to me the meaning of this legal term.)
5. Advokat se obraćao *sudiji* u oštroj tonu. (The lawyer spoke to the judge in a harsh tone.)
6. *Sudija* je bio veoma strog prema optuženom. (The judge was very strict with the defendant.)
7. Da bi postao *sudija*, potrebno je da ispunite određene uslove. (To become a judge, you need to meet certain requirements.)
8. *Sudijama* je potrebno puno znanja iz pravnih nauka. (Judges need a lot of knowledge in legal sciences.)
9. Ova sudija je poznata po svojoj nepristrasnosti i objektivnosti. (This judge is known for her impartiality and objectivity.)
10. Advokat se obratio *sudijama* sa novim dokazom. (The lawyer addressed the judges with new evidence.)

In English, the word "sudijo" translates to "judge", and "sudija" is the plural form of "judge".